/Chris_Langford.html}}\n\n{{1986/88/89/91 Hawthorn premiership players}}\n{{Hawthorn Football Club captains}}\n{{Hawthorn Team of The Century}}\n{{1987 All-Australian team}}\n{{1994 All-Australian team}}\n{{E. J. Whitten Medal winners}}\n{{navboxes\n| title = Chris Langford in Victorian State of Origin teams\n| titlestyle = background:#202231; color:white;\n| list1 ={{1989 Victoria State of Origin players}}\n{{1990 Victoria State of Origin players}}\n{{1990 Victoria 2nd XVIII State of Origin players}}\n{{1991 Victoria State of Origin players}}\n{{1992 Victoria State of Origin players}}\n{{1993 Victoria State of Origin players}}\n{{1994 Victoria State of Origin players}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Langford, Chris}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:People educated at Melbourne Grammar School]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia)]]\n[[Category:Hawthorn Football Club players]]\n[[Category:All-Australians (1953\u20131988)]]\n[[Category:Victorian State of Origin players]]\n[[Category:Australian Football Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:All-Australians (AFL)]]\n[[Category:E. J. Whitten Medal winners]]\n[[Category:Australia international rules football team players]]\n", "name_user": "2a01:c23:c035:1600:706b:a713:a66:ee15", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Langford"}
{"title_page": "Timothy Sykes", "text_new": "{{POV|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name         = Timothy Sykes\n|image        = Tim_Sykes.jpg\n|image_size   = \n|alt          = \n|caption      = \n|birth_name   = \n|birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1981|04|15}}\n|birth_place  = [[Orange, Connecticut]], U.S.\n|residence    = [[Miami Beach, Florida]], U.S.\n|alma_mater   = [[Tulane University]] \n|website      = {{URL|http://www.timothysykes.com/}}\n}}\n'''Timothy Sykes''' (born April 15, 1981) is a [[penny stock|penny stock trader]].<ref name=\"cnnmoney\">{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2013/12/16/investing/penny-stock-trader-millionaire/index.html?iid=HP_LN|title=Trader turns $1,500 to $1 million in 3 years|last=Yousuf|first=Hibah|date=December 16, 2013|publisher=CNN Money|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref name=nytimeshedge>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/12/08/business/media/08hedge.html?_r=0 |title=Culturally, Hedge Funds Go Public |author=de la Merced, Michael |publisher=New York Times |date=December 8, 2006}}</ref> He is best known for earning $1.65 million by [[day trading]] while attending [[Tulane University]].<ref name=nymag>{{cite news |url=https://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2007/11/timothy_sykes_will_not_be_stop.html |title=Timothy Sykes Will Not Be Stopped, Gosh Darn It |publisher=New York Magazine|date=November 1, 2007}}</ref><ref name=forbesinterview>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/feeds/options/2009/03/13/options20986.html|work=Forbes.com |title=Interview Central: Timothy Sykes, Part 1 |author=Neal, Jeff |date=March 13, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nSykes graduated from [[Tulane University]] in 2003 with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[philosophy]] and a minor in [[business]].<ref name=linkedin>{{cite web |url=http://www.linkedin.com/in/timothysykes |title=Timothy Sykes' LinkedIn Profile |publisher=LinkedIn}}</ref> While at Tulane, Sykes routinely cut class to day trade.<ref name=\"youngentrepreneur\">{{cite web|url=http://www.youngentrepreneur.com/blog/young-entrepreneurs-quit-being-such-babies-tim-sykes-tells-it-like-it-is/|title=Young Entrepreneurs: \"Quit being such babies!\" Tim Sykes Tells it Like it Is|author=Toren, Adam|date=October 25, 2011|publisher=YoungEntrepreneur.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101232834/http://www.youngentrepreneur.com/blog/young-entrepreneurs-quit-being-such-babies-tim-sykes-tells-it-like-it-is/|archive-date=November 1, 2012|url-status=dead|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> In 2003, during his senior year, he founded Cilantro Fund Management, a [[short selling|short bias]] hedge fund,<ref name=reuterscilantro>{{cite news |url=http://www.timothysykes.com/files/reuters07_26_06.pdf |title=US magazine toasts star traders aged 30 or younger |publisher=Reuters |date=July 27, 2006}}</ref><ref name=tulaneaward>{{cite web |url=http://tulane.edu/giving/news/two-students-win-sykes-award-recognizing-nontraditional-abilities-and-interests.cfm |title=Two students win Sykes Award recognizing nontraditional abilities and interests |author=Joe, Michael |publisher=Tulane.edu |date=May 8, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225213333/http://tulane.edu/giving/news/two-students-win-sykes-award-recognizing-nontraditional-abilities-and-interests.cfm |archivedate=February 25, 2013 }}</ref> using $1 million mostly from his friends and family.<ref name=thezeroes>{{cite book|author= Randall Lane|title= The Zeroes|location= page 56|publisher= Penguin Group|year= 2010|isbn= 978-1-59184-329-0|url= https://archive.org/details/zeroesmymisadven00lane}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, Sykes was included on ''[[Trader Monthly]]'''s \"30 Under 30\" list of up-and-coming traders in the market,<ref name=tradermonthly>{{cite news |url=http://www.timothysykes.com/files/tradermonthly30under30_08_06.pdf |title=30 under 30 |author=Barber, Andrew |publisher=Trader Monthly |date=August 2006}}</ref> a selection which editor Randall Lane later called \"our worst pick\" among the chosen honorees.<ref name=\"thezeroes\"/> Sykes claimed that the Cilantro Fund was \"the number one long-short microstock hedge fund in the country, according to Barclays\";<ref name=\"thezeroes\"/> Lane later discovered that the rating came from \"the Barclay Group,\" a small research company based in Fairfield, Iowa, and not the well-known [[Barclay's]] British bank.<ref name=barclay>{{cite web |url=http://toptenpk.com/5-things-you-should-know-about-tim-sykes/ |title=5 Things You Should Know about Tim Sykes |author= Thomassen, Lucilla |publisher=TopTenPK.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author= Randall Lane|title= The Zeroes|location= pages 151-153|publisher= Penguin Group|year= 2010|isbn= 978-1-59184-329-0|url= https://archive.org/details/zeroesmymisadven00lane}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008 Sykes decided to recreate his initial investing success by again starting with $12,415.<ref name=\"wunderkidback\">{{cite web|url=https://www.investmentnews.com/article/20071112/FREE/711120334/wunderkind-is-back|title=Wunderkid is Back|last=Hansard|first=Sara|date=November 12, 2007|publisher=Investment News}}</ref><ref name=prweb>{{cite web |url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2007/11/prweb565596.htm |title='Wall Street Warriors' TV Star Timothy Sykes Sets Up New & Transparent Challenge |publisher=PR Web |date=November 1, 2007}}</ref> He named the attempt Transparent Investment Management (TIM).<ref name=nymag/><ref name=huffpotim>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/eric-kuhn/from-bar-mitzvah-thousand_b_100061.html |title=From Bar Mitzvah Thousands to Bar Mitzvah Millions: Tim Sykes Launches New Site |author=Kuhn, Eric |publisher=Huffington Post |date=May 6, 2008}}</ref>\n\nSykes self-published ''An American Hedge Fund: How I Made $2 Million as a Stock Operator & Created a Hedge Fund'' in 2007.<ref>{{cite book|last=Sykes|first=Timothy|title=An American Hedge Fund: How I Made $2 Million as a Stock Operator & Created a Hedge Fund|year=2007|publisher=BullShip Press|isbn=0979549701|pages=235|url=https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0979549701/}}</ref> The book documented Sykes' experiences from day-trading in college to becoming a wealthy hedge fund manager.<ref name=oprahreview>{{cite web |url=http://www.oprah.com/oprahradio/An-American-Hedge-Fund |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100515204136/http://www.oprah.com/oprahradio/An-American-Hedge-Fund |archive-date=2010-05-15 |url-status=dead |title=An American Hedge Fund |author=Chatzky, Jean |publisher=Oprah.com |accessdate=2019-08-27}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Sykes created \"Miss Penny Stock,\" a financial beauty pageant among the female representatives for his brand and company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2012/08/23/stock-up-on-girls/|title=Stock up on girls|date=2012-08-23|website=Page Six|language=en|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/miss-penny-stock-pageant-2012-8|title=Penny Stock King Tim Sykes Is Hosting A Beauty Pageant Where Girls Will Parade Around In Bikinis And Cocktail Outfits|last=La Roche|first=Julia|date=Aug 23, 2012|publisher=Business Insider|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref>\n\n==Teaching and other projects==\nSykes currently works as a financial activist and educator.<ref name=\"nypost\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/pagesix/item_qxHXKGSnI3Bifa36DkuUUL|title=Party's Over for Hedge King|last=|first=|date=September 21, 2007|work=|access-date=2019-08-27|publisher=New York Post}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Sykes launched TimothySykes.com. It serves as its own personal blog and a website dedicated to teaching penny stock trading.<ref>https://www.timothysykes.com/penny-stocks/</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Sykes launched Investimonials.com, a website devoted to collecting user reviews of financial services, videos, and books, as well as financial brokers.<ref name=techcrunch>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2009/11/25/investimonials-timothy-sykes/ |title=Investimonials Wants To Be Your Guide To Quality Financial Products |author= Kincaid, Jason |publisher=Tech Crunch |date=November 25, 2009}}</ref>\n\nSykes co-founded Profit.ly in 2011, a social service with about 20,000 users that provides stock trade information online.<ref name=inc>{{cite news |url=http://www.inc.com/young-entrepreneur-council/best-advice-i-ever-got-timothy-sykes.html |title=Best Advice I Ever Got: Timothy Sykes |publisher=Inc. |date=June 1, 2011}}</ref> Sykes said the service serves two purposes: \"creating public track records for gurus, newsletter writers and students everyone to learn from both the wins and losses of other traders to benefit the entire industry.\"<ref name=forbesprofitly>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomanderson/2011/09/15/profit-ly-mines-the-masses-for-stock-trading-gold/ |title=Profit.ly Mines The Masses For Stock-Trading Gold |author=Anderson, Tom |publisher=Forbes |date=September 15, 2011}}</ref>\n\nSykes founded the Timothy Sykes Foundation, which has raised $600,000 and has partnered with [[Make-a-Wish Foundation]] and the [[Boys & Girls Clubs of America|Boys and Girls Club]].<ref>Rampton, John [http://www.inc.com/john-rampton/interview-with-timothy-sykes-the-man-who-wants-everyone-to-be-a-millionaire.html The Man Who Wants Everyone to Be a Millionaire] ''Inc.'' September 24, 2015</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Sykes donated $1 million to Pencils of Promise to help build 20 new primary schools across Ghana, Guatemala and Laos, to be completed between 2017 and 2018.<ref name=\"lh\">{{cite web|title=Make Money and Make an Impact with Tim Sykes|url=http://lewishowes.com/podcast/timothy-sykes2/|publisher=Lewis Howes}}</ref>\n\nSykes is one of the founders of Karmagawa, <ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/bryancollinseurope/2019/09/10/karmagawas-timothy-sykes-says-philanthropy-will-change-your-business/#106541802c1e</ref> a charity dedicated to helping animals, preserving natural resources, and assisting those in need around the world. In 2019, Karmagawa worked with documentarian Amir Zakeri to create a documentary called \"50 Minutes to Save the World,\"<ref>https://conservationmag.org/en/video-page/50-minutes-to-save-the-world-youtube-movie-on-conserving-our-oceans-hit-1-1m-views-in-1-week</ref> which documents the state of the coral reef.\n\n==Controversy==\n\nSykes clearly decides to edit his own wikipedia page because he thinks he is important. He thinks there has been people who publicly criticized various businesses and celebrities, including [[Shaquille O'Neal]]<ref name=bi>{{cite web|last=Veneziani|first=Vince|title=Tim Sykes: I Dare Shaq To Take Me To Court!|url=http://articles.businessinsider.com/2010-03-03/wall_street/29981469_1_mailer-stock-price-blogging|work=Business Insider|accessdate=7 January 2013|date=March 3, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130114131353/http://articles.businessinsider.com/2010-03-03/wall_street/29981469_1_mailer-stock-price-blogging|archivedate=14 January 2013}}</ref> and [[Justin Bieber]],<ref name=mfool/><ref name=msn>{{cite web|last=Peterson|first=Kim|title=Justin Bieber's penny-stock trouble|url=http://money.msn.com/exchange-traded-fund/article.aspx?post=158da049-d085-455a-9f98-df126b4ebaf0|publisher=MSN Money|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110527100004/http://money.msn.com/exchange-traded-fund/article.aspx?post=158da049-d085-455a-9f98-df126b4ebaf0|archivedate=27 May 2011}}</ref> for promoting \"[[pump and dump]]\" schemes,<ref name=mfool>{{cite web|last=Cunningham|first=Brandon|title=The Curious Case of Justin Bieber and Options Media Group (aka PhoneGuard)|url=http://www.fool.com/investing/general/2011/05/20/the-curious-case-of-justin-bieber-and-options-medi.aspx?source=isesitlnk0000008|publisher=Motley Fool}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2009/09/17/not-spongeworthy/|title=Not Spongeworthy|last=Whitehouse|first=Kaja|date=2009-09-17|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/spongetech-execs-charged-with-fraud-2010-5|title=SpongeTech CEO Arrested For Fraud A Week After Suing Short-Seller|last=Veneziani|first=Vince|date=May 5, 2010|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20110411/BLOGS02/304119998/bill-for-spongetech-fraud-52-million|title=Bill for Spongetech fraud: $52 million|last=Elstein|first=Aaron|date=2011-04-11|website=Crain's New York Business|language=en|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> in which an investor purchases stock, hypes others into buying that stock to inflate its price, then sells the shares at a higher price and shorts the profit from the resulting decline.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.timothysykes.com/}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sykes, Timothy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American finance and investment writers]]\n[[Category:American investors]]\n[[Category:American Jews]]\n[[Category:American hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:American stock traders]]\n[[Category:Stock and commodity market managers]]\n[[Category:Tulane University alumni]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{POV|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name         = Timothy Sykes\n|image        = Tim_Sykes.jpg\n|image_size   = \n|alt          = \n|caption      = \n|birth_name   = \n|birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1981|04|15}}\n|birth_place  = [[Orange, Connecticut]], U.S.\n|residence    = [[Miami Beach, Florida]], U.S.\n|alma_mater   = [[Tulane University]] \n|website      = {{URL|http://www.timothysykes.com/}}\n}}\n'''Timothy Sykes''' (born April 15, 1981) is a [[penny stock|penny stock trader]].<ref name=\"cnnmoney\">{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2013/12/16/investing/penny-stock-trader-millionaire/index.html?iid=HP_LN|title=Trader turns $1,500 to $1 million in 3 years|last=Yousuf|first=Hibah|date=December 16, 2013|publisher=CNN Money|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref name=nytimeshedge>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/12/08/business/media/08hedge.html?_r=0 |title=Culturally, Hedge Funds Go Public |author=de la Merced, Michael |publisher=New York Times |date=December 8, 2006}}</ref> He is best known for earning $1.65 million by [[day trading]] while attending [[Tulane University]].<ref name=nymag>{{cite news |url=https://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2007/11/timothy_sykes_will_not_be_stop.html |title=Timothy Sykes Will Not Be Stopped, Gosh Darn It |publisher=New York Magazine|date=November 1, 2007}}</ref><ref name=forbesinterview>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/feeds/options/2009/03/13/options20986.html|work=Forbes.com |title=Interview Central: Timothy Sykes, Part 1 |author=Neal, Jeff |date=March 13, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nSykes graduated from [[Tulane University]] in 2003 with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[philosophy]] and a minor in [[business]].<ref name=linkedin>{{cite web |url=http://www.linkedin.com/in/timothysykes |title=Timothy Sykes' LinkedIn Profile |publisher=LinkedIn}}</ref> While at Tulane, Sykes routinely cut class to day trade.<ref name=\"youngentrepreneur\">{{cite web|url=http://www.youngentrepreneur.com/blog/young-entrepreneurs-quit-being-such-babies-tim-sykes-tells-it-like-it-is/|title=Young Entrepreneurs: \"Quit being such babies!\" Tim Sykes Tells it Like it Is|author=Toren, Adam|date=October 25, 2011|publisher=YoungEntrepreneur.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101232834/http://www.youngentrepreneur.com/blog/young-entrepreneurs-quit-being-such-babies-tim-sykes-tells-it-like-it-is/|archive-date=November 1, 2012|url-status=dead|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> In 2003, during his senior year, he founded Cilantro Fund Management, a [[short selling|short bias]] hedge fund,<ref name=reuterscilantro>{{cite news |url=http://www.timothysykes.com/files/reuters07_26_06.pdf |title=US magazine toasts star traders aged 30 or younger |publisher=Reuters |date=July 27, 2006}}</ref><ref name=tulaneaward>{{cite web |url=http://tulane.edu/giving/news/two-students-win-sykes-award-recognizing-nontraditional-abilities-and-interests.cfm |title=Two students win Sykes Award recognizing nontraditional abilities and interests |author=Joe, Michael |publisher=Tulane.edu |date=May 8, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225213333/http://tulane.edu/giving/news/two-students-win-sykes-award-recognizing-nontraditional-abilities-and-interests.cfm |archivedate=February 25, 2013 }}</ref> using $1 million mostly from his friends and family.<ref name=thezeroes>{{cite book|author= Randall Lane|title= The Zeroes|location= page 56|publisher= Penguin Group|year= 2010|isbn= 978-1-59184-329-0|url= https://archive.org/details/zeroesmymisadven00lane}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, Sykes was included on ''[[Trader Monthly]]'''s \"30 Under 30\" list of up-and-coming traders in the market,<ref name=tradermonthly>{{cite news |url=http://www.timothysykes.com/files/tradermonthly30under30_08_06.pdf |title=30 under 30 |author=Barber, Andrew |publisher=Trader Monthly |date=August 2006}}</ref> a selection which editor Randall Lane later called \"our worst pick\" among the chosen honorees.<ref name=\"thezeroes\"/> Sykes claimed that the Cilantro Fund was \"the number one long-short microstock hedge fund in the country, according to Barclays\";<ref name=\"thezeroes\"/> Lane later discovered that the rating came from \"the Barclay Group,\" a small research company based in Fairfield, Iowa, and not the well-known [[Barclay's]] British bank.<ref name=barclay>{{cite web |url=http://toptenpk.com/5-things-you-should-know-about-tim-sykes/ |title=5 Things You Should Know about Tim Sykes |author= Thomassen, Lucilla |publisher=TopTenPK.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author= Randall Lane|title= The Zeroes|location= pages 151-153|publisher= Penguin Group|year= 2010|isbn= 978-1-59184-329-0|url= https://archive.org/details/zeroesmymisadven00lane}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008 Sykes decided to recreate his initial investing success by again starting with $12,415.<ref name=\"wunderkidback\">{{cite web|url=https://www.investmentnews.com/article/20071112/FREE/711120334/wunderkind-is-back|title=Wunderkid is Back|last=Hansard|first=Sara|date=November 12, 2007|publisher=Investment News}}</ref><ref name=prweb>{{cite web |url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2007/11/prweb565596.htm |title='Wall Street Warriors' TV Star Timothy Sykes Sets Up New & Transparent Challenge |publisher=PR Web |date=November 1, 2007}}</ref> He named the attempt Transparent Investment Management (TIM).<ref name=nymag/><ref name=huffpotim>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/eric-kuhn/from-bar-mitzvah-thousand_b_100061.html |title=From Bar Mitzvah Thousands to Bar Mitzvah Millions: Tim Sykes Launches New Site |author=Kuhn, Eric |publisher=Huffington Post |date=May 6, 2008}}</ref>\n\nSykes self-published ''An American Hedge Fund: How I Made $2 Million as a Stock Operator & Created a Hedge Fund'' in 2007.<ref>{{cite book|last=Sykes|first=Timothy|title=An American Hedge Fund: How I Made $2 Million as a Stock Operator & Created a Hedge Fund|year=2007|publisher=BullShip Press|isbn=0979549701|pages=235|url=https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0979549701/}}</ref> The book documented Sykes' experiences from day-trading in college to becoming a wealthy hedge fund manager.<ref name=oprahreview>{{cite web |url=http://www.oprah.com/oprahradio/An-American-Hedge-Fund |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100515204136/http://www.oprah.com/oprahradio/An-American-Hedge-Fund |archive-date=2010-05-15 |url-status=dead |title=An American Hedge Fund |author=Chatzky, Jean |publisher=Oprah.com |accessdate=2019-08-27}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Sykes created \"Miss Penny Stock,\" a financial beauty pageant among the female representatives for his brand and company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2012/08/23/stock-up-on-girls/|title=Stock up on girls|date=2012-08-23|website=Page Six|language=en|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/miss-penny-stock-pageant-2012-8|title=Penny Stock King Tim Sykes Is Hosting A Beauty Pageant Where Girls Will Parade Around In Bikinis And Cocktail Outfits|last=La Roche|first=Julia|date=Aug 23, 2012|publisher=Business Insider|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref>\n\n==Teaching and other projects==\nSykes currently works as a financial activist and educator.<ref name=\"nypost\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/pagesix/item_qxHXKGSnI3Bifa36DkuUUL|title=Party's Over for Hedge King|last=|first=|date=September 21, 2007|work=|access-date=2019-08-27|publisher=New York Post}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Sykes launched TimothySykes.com. It serves as its own personal blog and a website dedicated to teaching penny stock trading.<ref>https://www.timothysykes.com/penny-stocks/</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Sykes launched Investimonials.com, a website devoted to collecting user reviews of financial services, videos, and books, as well as financial brokers.<ref name=techcrunch>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2009/11/25/investimonials-timothy-sykes/ |title=Investimonials Wants To Be Your Guide To Quality Financial Products |author= Kincaid, Jason |publisher=Tech Crunch |date=November 25, 2009}}</ref>\n\nSykes co-founded Profit.ly in 2011, a social service with about 20,000 users that provides stock trade information online.<ref name=inc>{{cite news |url=http://www.inc.com/young-entrepreneur-council/best-advice-i-ever-got-timothy-sykes.html |title=Best Advice I Ever Got: Timothy Sykes |publisher=Inc. |date=June 1, 2011}}</ref> Sykes said the service serves two purposes: \"creating public track records for gurus, newsletter writers and students everyone to learn from both the wins and losses of other traders to benefit the entire industry.\"<ref name=forbesprofitly>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomanderson/2011/09/15/profit-ly-mines-the-masses-for-stock-trading-gold/ |title=Profit.ly Mines The Masses For Stock-Trading Gold |author=Anderson, Tom |publisher=Forbes |date=September 15, 2011}}</ref>\n\nSykes founded the Timothy Sykes Foundation, which has raised $600,000 and has partnered with [[Make-a-Wish Foundation]] and the [[Boys & Girls Clubs of America|Boys and Girls Club]].<ref>Rampton, John [http://www.inc.com/john-rampton/interview-with-timothy-sykes-the-man-who-wants-everyone-to-be-a-millionaire.html The Man Who Wants Everyone to Be a Millionaire] ''Inc.'' September 24, 2015</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Sykes donated $1 million to Pencils of Promise to help build 20 new primary schools across Ghana, Guatemala and Laos, to be completed between 2017 and 2018.<ref name=\"lh\">{{cite web|title=Make Money and Make an Impact with Tim Sykes|url=http://lewishowes.com/podcast/timothy-sykes2/|publisher=Lewis Howes}}</ref>\n\nSykes is one of the founders of Karmagawa, <ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/bryancollinseurope/2019/09/10/karmagawas-timothy-sykes-says-philanthropy-will-change-your-business/#106541802c1e</ref> a charity dedicated to helping animals, preserving natural resources, and assisting those in need around the world. In 2019, Karmagawa worked with documentarian Amir Zakeri to create a documentary called \"50 Minutes to Save the World,\"<ref>https://conservationmag.org/en/video-page/50-minutes-to-save-the-world-youtube-movie-on-conserving-our-oceans-hit-1-1m-views-in-1-week</ref> which documents the state of the coral reef.\n\n==Controversy==\n\nSykes has publicly criticized various businesses and celebrities, including [[Shaquille O'Neal]]<ref name=bi>{{cite web|last=Veneziani|first=Vince|title=Tim Sykes: I Dare Shaq To Take Me To Court!|url=http://articles.businessinsider.com/2010-03-03/wall_street/29981469_1_mailer-stock-price-blogging|work=Business Insider|accessdate=7 January 2013|date=March 3, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130114131353/http://articles.businessinsider.com/2010-03-03/wall_street/29981469_1_mailer-stock-price-blogging|archivedate=14 January 2013}}</ref> and [[Justin Bieber]],<ref name=mfool/><ref name=msn>{{cite web|last=Peterson|first=Kim|title=Justin Bieber's penny-stock trouble|url=http://money.msn.com/exchange-traded-fund/article.aspx?post=158da049-d085-455a-9f98-df126b4ebaf0|publisher=MSN Money|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110527100004/http://money.msn.com/exchange-traded-fund/article.aspx?post=158da049-d085-455a-9f98-df126b4ebaf0|archivedate=27 May 2011}}</ref> for promoting \"[[pump and dump]]\" schemes,<ref name=mfool>{{cite web|last=Cunningham|first=Brandon|title=The Curious Case of Justin Bieber and Options Media Group (aka PhoneGuard)|url=http://www.fool.com/investing/general/2011/05/20/the-curious-case-of-justin-bieber-and-options-medi.aspx?source=isesitlnk0000008|publisher=Motley Fool}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2009/09/17/not-spongeworthy/|title=Not Spongeworthy|last=Whitehouse|first=Kaja|date=2009-09-17|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/spongetech-execs-charged-with-fraud-2010-5|title=SpongeTech CEO Arrested For Fraud A Week After Suing Short-Seller|last=Veneziani|first=Vince|date=May 5, 2010|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20110411/BLOGS02/304119998/bill-for-spongetech-fraud-52-million|title=Bill for Spongetech fraud: $52 million|last=Elstein|first=Aaron|date=2011-04-11|website=Crain's New York Business|language=en|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> in which an investor purchases stock, hypes others into buying that stock to inflate its price, then sells the shares at a higher price and shorts the profit from the resulting decline.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.timothysykes.com/}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sykes, Timothy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American finance and investment writers]]\n[[Category:American investors]]\n[[Category:American Jews]]\n[[Category:American hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:American stock traders]]\n[[Category:Stock and commodity market managers]]\n[[Category:Tulane University alumni]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n", "name_user": "108.51.104.192", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eControversy:Add facts)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timothy_Sykes"}
{"title_page": "Jessie (2011 TV series)", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Jessie\n| image                = Jessie logo.png\n| image_alt            = <!-- Alt text should be provided per MOS:ALT. -->\n| genre                = [[Comedy]]\n| creator              = [[Pamela Eells O'Connell]]\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Debby Ryan]]\n* [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]]\n* [[Cameron Boyce]]\n* [[Karan Brar]]\n* [[Skai Jackson]]\n* [[Kevin Chamberlin]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = {{Plainlist|\n* Toby Gad <!-- do not link to [[Toby Gad]]. This is not the same person! -->\n* [[Lindy Robbins]]\n}}\n| opentheme            = \"Hey Jessie\" performed by Debby Ryan\n| composer             = {{Plainlist|\n* John Adair\n* Steve Hampton\n}}\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 4\n| num_episodes         = 98\n| list_episodes        = List of Jessie episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{Plainlist|\n* Pamela Eells O'Connell\n* [[Adam I. Lapidus|Adam Lapidus]]\n}}\n| camera               = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Videotape]] ([[Filmizing|filmized]])\n* [[Multi-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n}}\n| runtime              = 22\u201325 minutes\n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[It's a Laugh Productions]]\n* [[Bon Mot Productions]]\n}}\n| network              = [[Disney Channel]]\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[720p]]\n| audio_format         = [[5.1 surround sound]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2011|9|30}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2015|10|16}}\n| related              = ''[[Bunk'd]]''\n| website              = https://disneynow.go.com/shows/jessie\n}}\n\n'''''Jessie''''' is an American [[comedy]] television series created by [[Pamela Eells O'Connell]] that aired on [[Disney Channel]] from September 30, 2011 to October 16, 2015. The series stars [[Debby Ryan]], [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]], [[Cameron Boyce]], [[Karan Brar]], [[Skai Jackson]], and [[Kevin Chamberlin]].\n\n== Plot ==\nThe series follows Jessie Prescott (Debby Ryan), a young woman from a small town with big dreams who, rebelling against her strict father, decides to leave the [[Fort Hood|military base]] in [[Texas]] where she grew up and moves to [[New York City]]. She accepts a job as a nanny and moves into a multimillion-dollar penthouse on the [[Upper West Side]] with the wealthy Ross family which includes [[Jet set|jet-setting]] parents Morgan and Christina Ross and their four rambunctious children: Emma, Luke, Ravi, and Zuri, along with the family pet, Mr. Kipling, a seven-foot [[Asian water monitor]] lizard, that was later revealed to be a female. With a whole new world of experiences open to her, Jessie embarks on new adventures in the big city as she grows to rely on the love and support of the children in her care. Assisting her are Bertram ([[Kevin Chamberlin]]), the family's lazy and sarcastic butler, and Tony ([[Chris Galya]]), the building's 20-year-old doorman.\n\n== Characters ==\n\n=== Main ===\n[[File:Cast_of_Disneys_Jessie.jpg|thumb|Main characters of ''Jessie'' L-R: Bertram, Zuri, Luke, Jessie, Emma and Ravi (with his pet lizard Mr. Kipling)]] \n*{{visible anchor|Jessie Prescott}} ([[Debby Ryan]]) is an idealistic and resourceful girl from the military base of [[Fort Hood]], Texas. As a recent high school graduate rebelling against her strict father who wanted her to join the army, Jessie moved to [[New York City]] to realize her dreams of stardom but, due to an unexpected turn of events, ends up becoming a nanny to the four Ross children. Even though at times both Jessie and the Ross kids annoy each other, they all deeply care for one another and Jessie is even shown to be sometimes overprotective. Later her last name is revealed to be Prescott. In the episode \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep29|Make New Friends, but Hide the Old]]\", she reveals that she is an only child. Jessie also has a complicated love life. Her boyfriend stories are frequently mentioned, and only in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep58|The Rosses Get Real]]\" are they called something other than boring and pathetic. Her mother has never been seen but is mentioned in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep52|G.I. Jessie]]\".\n*{{visible anchor|Emma Ross}} ([[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]]) is a diva, somewhat ditsy, cynical girl, eager to reorder the world to the way she sees it. Emma is the oldest child of the Ross family, and Morgan and Christina's only biological child. Emma spends most of her time with Zuri and doesn't appreciate her brother Luke. In the second season, she acts as Kitty Couture, an anonymous fashion [[vlog]]ger, and starts to get along with Luke more. She and Ravi also spend time together as brother and sister. It is revealed in the episode titled ''Karate Kid-tastrophe'' that her full name is Emma Evangeline Ross.\n*{{visible anchor|Luke Ross}} ([[Cameron Boyce]]) is a laid back, flirty, crafty boy who was born in [[Detroit]] and has a passion for video games, break-dancing, and causing mischief around the penthouse while also being sarcastic at times. He considers himself a \"ladies' man\", having taken a liking to Jessie in particular. Luke even tried to date her in the first few episodes. Luke is the second oldest of the Ross children. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep15|The Kid Whisperer]]\", his full name is revealed to be Lucas. He spends a lot of time with his brother, Ravi, and has a close bond with Bertram as well. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep57|Lizard Scales and Wrestling Tales]]\", his middle name is revealed as Philbert, named after his grandpa.\n*{{visible anchor|Ravi Ross}} ([[Karan Brar]]) is a gentle, intelligent and courteous boy, born and raised for ten and a half years in [[West Bengal]], India, and the newest addition of the Ross family. He is imbued with the culture of his beloved homeland but is thrilled with his new life in the United States. He is the third oldest of the Ross children and also the most intelligent. He spends most of his time with Luke but appreciates his sisters all the same. He also spends time with his lizard Mr. Kipling\u2014later revealed to be Mrs. Kipling\u2014which he brought from India.\n*{{visible anchor|Zuri Ross}} ([[Skai Jackson]]) is a sassy, strong-willed, quick-witted and talkative girl who was brought to NYC from her birth country of Uganda. She is highly creative with a penchant for rainbows, unicorns, mermaids, and country music, and has many stuffed animals and imaginary friends. She is the youngest of the Ross children. She has close bonds with Jessie, Emma, and her imaginary friends. Zuri later lets go of all of her imaginary friends, hinting that she's maturing as an adolescent.\n*{{visible anchor|Bertram}}<!-- do not add Winkle as last name as it is not how this character is credited --> ([[Kevin Chamberlin]]) is the Ross family's butler. He is grouchy and often very lazy, though begrudgingly helps Jessie navigate her job as nanny to the four Ross children. In \"The Kid Whisperer\", his [[hoarding]] obsession is revealed. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep20|Tempest in a Teacup]]\", it is revealed that Bertram is claustrophobic. He also has a passion for opera music and boy bands. Even though the Ross kids, as well as Jessie, get on his nerves sometimes, he deeply cares about them. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep5|One-Day Wonders]]\", it is revealed that his last name is Winkle.\n\n=== Recurring ===\n*Christina Ross ([[Christina Moore]]) is the mother of the four Ross children and a former [[supermodel]] turned [[business magnate]].\n*Tony ({{visible anchor|Chris Galya}}) is the doorman in the building where the Ross family lives who has strong feelings for Jessie and helps her navigate her adventures in the big city. He also starts to date Jessie in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep13|The Princess and the Pea Brain]]\". They later break up in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep51|Break-Up and Shape-Up]]\". In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep33|The Trouble with Tessie]]\", it is revealed that his last name is Chiccolini. His parents own a restaurant in Little Italy. A recurring joke on the show has Jessie and Bertram asking the kids where they found some strange, but needed, things, and the response is invariably \"Tony knows a guy\".\n*Morgan Ross ([[Chip Esten|Charles Esten]]) is the father of the four Ross children and a famous movie director. The pilot episode reveals he is friends with [[George Lucas]]. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep25|Gotcha Day]]\", he thought that a chili slip 'n' slide was a great idea.\n*{{visible anchor|Mrs. Kipling}}, formerly Mr. Kipling{{refn|Press releases stated \"Ms. Kipling\" while the actual episode used \"Mrs. Kipling\".|name=MsKiplingPR|group=note}} (Frank) is the Ross family's house pet, a seven-foot [[Asian water monitor]] lizard, that Ravi brought from India when he came to America. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep26|The Secret Life of Mr. Kipling]]\", it is revealed that ''he'' is actually a female monitor lizard and has laid twelve eggs. The names of Mrs. Kipling's twelve babies are Mowgli, Sanjay, Gupta, Slumdog, Kumar, Ravi Jr., Scooter, Rikki, Tikki, Tavi, Mohandas, and Padma.\n*Rhoda Chesterfield ([[Carolyn Hennesy]]) is the cold-hearted head of the city condominium board in the building where the Ross family lives. Her first spat with Jessie and the Ross clan involved Mrs. Kipling tearing her clothes up in the elevator. She dislikes anyone who is not rich, who is under 20, or who is less self-absorbed than herself. This sadly doesn't stop her from repeatedly hitting on Bertram, lavishing too much affection on her chihuahua, Zeus, or constantly calling Jessie by the wrong name. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep30|101 Lizards]]\", it is revealed that she has a daughter, Cassandra, and owns a lizard sanctuary. It is also revealed in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep73|Between the Swoon and New York City]]\" that she has a son named Brooks. It is also revealed that she has been married more than once. She had no romantic feelings toward her first husband and married him for his money. Despite her rivalry against the Ross family, it is shown in \"101 Lizards\" that she seems to have a soft spot for Emma.\n*Stuart Wooten ([[J.J. Totah]]) is a quick-witted, yet love-struck, kid. He has a huge crush on Zuri and is a good friend to the Ross brothers. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep46|Quitting Cold Koala]]\", he and Zuri go on a romantic picnic, implying that they have a [[romantic friendship|relationship]]. Stuart is usually nice and kind, but he's able to show a blunt side when he wants to, like Zuri does, as seen in later episodes. In \"Quitting Cold Koala\", he attempts to make Zuri jealous and hint that she likes him back. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep47|Panic Attack Room]]\", he addresses the Ross brothers as ''neanderthals'', annoyed that they interrupted his board game date with Luke and Ravi's younger sister. He also seems to own a pair of pants for every single occasion, such as \"picnic pants\" and \"panic room pants\". In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep64|Acting with the Frenemy]]\", he is jealous when Zuri has a crush on Shane, Luke's new member, and they have a dance-off for Zuri. He stands up for her, creating romance between the two. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep67|Where's Zuri?]]\", after undergoing transformation from Stuart to Stu-Dog by his new nanny, Zuri falls for him.\n*Officer Petey (Joey Richter) is a police officer who is strangely obsessed with the performing arts. He is not a very good police officer. In fact, he wanted to be an actor. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep37|Pain in the Rear Window]]\", it is revealed that he has very little physical strength and cannot tolerate the sight of bruised skin, let alone blood. It is also revealed that he did not go to a police academy.\n*Rosie ([[Kelly Gould]]) is Emma's best friend who lives in a crime-ridden area of the city but is actually a nice girl. She used Emma to lampoon a nasty girl in \"Make New Friends, but Hide the Old\"; however, since Emma and Rosie both hate the bully, they become friends by the end of the episode. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep31|Trashin' Fashion]]\", she is Emma's camera girl for their blog. Their friendship is threatened when Rosie stands up for Bryn in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep41|Kids Don't Wanna Be Shunned]]\".\n*Agatha ([[Jennifer Veal]]) is an unattractive, arrogant British nanny who frequently locks horns with Jessie and the Ross children. During their first meeting, she attempts to ban Zuri and Jessie from Central Park. Zuri and Jessie ignore Agatha and keep coming back, so Agatha starts posting mean things, saying that Jessie is a bad nanny on her website \"Toddler Tattler\". Zuri, Jessie, and Christina stand up to Agatha and Agatha shuts down her website. Agatha has a twin sister, Angela, revealed in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep19|Evil Times Two]]\", who is even more dishonest and tries to steal Jessie's job, but Jessie and the Ross kids stand up to her and she goes back to England. This was the only time Agatha, who despises the long-favored Angela, was on the same side as Jessie. Officer Petey met Agatha at a fair in the park, and thought she was cute until he learned her mole and snaggle-tooth were not part of her costume.\n*Connie Thompson ([[Sierra McCormick]]) is an insane girl with an obsessive crush on Luke. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep7|Creepy Connie Comes a Callin']]\", she tutors Luke but also tries to flirt with him. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep23|Creepy Connie's Curtain Call]]\", she auditions for the school play written by Jessie. She causes \"accidents\" to the female lead and understudies, so she can get the lead role and kiss Luke. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep63|Creepy Connie 3: The Creepening]]\", she hires an actress, Mackenzie ([[G. Hannelius]]), to pretend to be obsessed with Luke so he'll like Connie. In \"Creepy Connie's Curtain Call\", she starts dating Ravi but pretends to not remember him in \"Creepy Connie 3: The Creepening\". She is also an avid fan of [[Harry Potter]].\n*Boomer ([[Lombardo Boyar]]) is Emma's new boss and Connie's uncle. He is shown as a hardworking and easily persuaded man.\n*Brooks Wentworth ([[Pierson Fode]]) is Jessie's new boyfriend who later becomes Jessie's fianc\u00e9. He got a job in Africa and asked Jessie to get married as soon as possible. She decides to go with him, but the kids find out and are extremely upset. On their wedding day, Jessie realizes she is not ready to be married and breaks up with Brooks. Jessie stays in New York and Brooks leaves for Africa. They later meet up and Jessie is surprised to learn Brooks has moved on.\n\n=== Guest stars ===\n*Bryn Breitbart ([[Katherine McNamara]]) appeared in \"Kids Don't Wanna Be Shunned\", where she attempts to steal Emma's friends by pretending she is of Danish royalty. In \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep50|Diary of a Mad Newswoman]]\", Emma forgives Bryn and they become coworkers on Ravi's school news show. She tries to ruin Emma by feeding her a fake story, but Emma, Luke, and Ravi catch her in her act. Luke had a crush on her before her plot was revealed.\n*Shaylee Michaels ([[Maia Mitchell]]) is a successful Australian actress who befriends Jessie, casting her as her stunt double in her latest film in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep36|Jessie's Big Break]]\". Her boyfriend McD ([[John DeLuca]]), who is also the director of the movie, attempts to flirt and kiss Jessie and later turn Shaylee against Jessie by claiming Jessie was lying to her. Jessie ultimately proves her innocence with Luke's camera footage proving that McD had indeed flirted with Jessie. Shaylee is the only girl in the series whom Luke has had a crush on big enough to rival his crush on Jessie.\n*Ms. Falkenberg ([[Cheri Oteri]]) is Zuri\u2019s quirky but overly strict third-grade teacher, appearing in the episode \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep35|Teacher's Pest]]\". Jessie serves as Ms. Falkenberg\u2019s classroom aide.\n*[[Chris Bosh]] appeared as himself in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep34|Say Yes to the Messy Dress]]\". He keeps his stinky white socks from the tenth grade as a sign of good luck, even though Luke disagrees with him and tries to sabotage his chance to win a basketball game against the [[New York Knicks]].\n*[[Adam Sandler]] appeared as himself in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep45|Punch Dumped Love]]\", making spare change. He claims he wants to go by his nickname \"Thunder\".\n*Ted ([[Spencer Boldman]]) appeared in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep51|Break-Up and Shake-Up]]\" as one of Jessie's old boyfriends. According to Jessie, he was ugly when she dated and dumped him and is now a male model. Jessie attempts to use him to make Tony jealous. In the end, he goes out with Victoria ([[Lulu Antariksa]]), and Tony and Jessie break up.\n*Vic ([[Lulu Antariksa]]) appears in \"Break-Up and Shake-Up\", where Tony trains her to become a doorwoman, causing Jessie to become jealous of them. In the end, Vic goes out with one of Jessie\u2019s exes, Ted.\n*Max Bauer (Matthew Timmons) is Jessie's young agent who appears in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep54|Caught Purple Handed]]\", where he says that he is living in his mother's basement and has to pay her rent. He gets Jessie her first infomercial job as a hand model, but he is fired with her after Jessie botches the job. Jessie later thanks Max for his faith in her and agrees to let him stay as her agent.\n*Earl ([[Garrett Clayton]]) appeared in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep56|The Blind Date, the Cheapskate, and the Primate]]\", where he is the garbage man in the apartment building.\n*Maybelle ([[Stefanie Scott]]) is the new girl in the Ross's apartment building. She appears in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep61|Hoedown Showdown]]\", where she hog-ties Emma's new \"soul mate\" after he asks her out knowing Emma likes him.\n*Mackenzie ([[G. Hannelius]]) is another creepy girl in school along with Connie. She appears in \"Creepy Connie 3 : The Creepening\", where she has a psycho crush on Luke just like Connie. She is very creepy by making a bracelet of baby teeth for Luke and also wanting Luke to date her just like Connie. However, Connie and Mack wrestle after they find out they both like Luke. Later, it is revealed that Mack was an actress and really did not have a crush on Luke.\n*Mrs. Arthur ([[Jo Anne Worley]]) is Nana Banana in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep6|Zuri's New Old Friend]]\".\n*[[Michelle Obama]] appeared as herself in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep65|From the White House to Our House]]\", where she is called by Zuri because Zuri wants her friend Taylor's mother to be home for Taylor's tenth birthday.\n*[[Mr. Moseby]] ([[Phill Lewis]]) appeared in \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep83|Karate Kid-tastrophe]]\", where it is revealed he became the New York Tipton's hotel manager after the events of [[The Suite Life on Deck]]. Jessie accidentally runs into him while Emma is holed up in a room. Mr. Moseby later gives Jessie advice on how to deal with teenagers like Emma.\n*Madeline ([[Francesca Capaldi]]) appeared in What A Steal. She reveals herself to be a thief with her brother Scott.\n*[[Chris Paul]] as himself appeared in Basket Cases. He was coaching Ravi how to play basketball.\n*The Vamps as Themselves appeared in Dance, Dance, Resolution as they performed at the school dance.\n*Kim/Delpina ([[Meaghan Martin]] from Camp Rock) appeared in Rossed at Sea Part 1. She appeared to be a mermaid. Later, she was revealed to have a memory loss in the water and revealed herself as Kim, not a mermaid.\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nThe series was created by [[Pamela Eells O'Connell]], who had had previous experience with the \"nanny\" sitcom formula, starting her career as a writer on the series ''[[Charles in Charge]]'' and serving as co-executive producer on ''[[The Nanny]]'', before working with Debby Ryan on ''[[The Suite Life on Deck]]''.<ref name=\"IMDb.com\" /><ref name=\"SheKnows.com\" /><ref name=\"PopCulturePassionistas.com 2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/PCPassionistas?feature=mhee#p/u/8/c8i3nLYzdPg|title=An interview with Kevin Chamberlin from \"Jessie\"|date=September 27, 2011|work=PopCulturePassionistas.com}}</ref> O'Connell is said to have developed ''Jessie'' specifically to showcase Ryan's talent.<ref name=\"Star-Telegram\" /> In an interview with the ''[[Star-Telegram]]'', Ryan explained how the concept originated: \"(O'Connell) and I were throwing ideas back and forth when ''The Suite Life'' was coming to an end, and she came up with this. I was absolutely captivated. Then Disney looked at the script and the show runner (O'Connell) and myself and they were like: 'Awesome. We like it. You're on in the fall'\".<ref name=\"Star-Telegram\" /> In interviews with ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', Disney Channel President [[Gary Marsh]] spoke of working with Ryan again: \"It's been thrilling to watch Debby grow from an unknown actress to one of our top stars. Debby is a talented young actress who connects to a wide fanbase because she's genuine, relatable and aspirational all at once. Our viewers have followed her from ''[[The Suite Life on Deck]]'' to ''[[16 Wishes]]'', and we're pleased to be working with her again.\"<ref name=\"Variety 2\" /><ref name=\"Variety 1\" /> Jessie was the first main character to be engaged on the Disney Channel. There was a four-part episode about the engagement.<ref name=AP20140416>{{cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/tv/255526811.html|title='Jessie' says yes, as first Disney Channel character becomes engaged|date=April 16, 2014|first=Lynn|last=Elber|newspaper=Associated Press|via=StarTribune|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6OxmI1TyO?url=http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/tv/255526811.html#|archivedate=April 20, 2014|url-status=dead|access-date=April 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n<!-- If image changed the imagemap will need to be redone -->\n<imagemap>\nFile:Jessie_Cast.jpg|thumb|The cast in December 2011<br /><small>(use cursor to identify)</small>\npoly 2432 1306 2023 2720 2910 2720 2880 1896 2749 1355 [[Skai Jackson]]\npoly 1058 1121 809 1681 848 2720 1257 2720 1433 1979 1384 1145 [[Karan Brar]]\npoly 2627 892 2651 1301 2934 2705 3114 2734 3163 1462 2900 931 [[Cameron Boyce]]\npoly 2739 346 2822 887 3144 2710 3650 2729 3802 1423 3538 770 3090 273 [[#Chris Galya|Chris Galya]]\npoly 1482 502 1316 1048 1496 2700 1808 2720 1906 1642 1847 546 [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]]\npoly 2096 331 1896 1019 1847 2720 2027 2729 2588 1277 2603 882 2451 341 [[Debby Ryan]]\npoly 799 546 93 2276 317 2724 804 2720 819 1720 1262 960 1155 560 [[Mingle Media TV Network|Mingle Media TV reporter Kristyn Burtt]]\ndesc bottom-left\n</imagemap>\n\nWith Ryan signed on, [[Disney Channel]] began the search to cast the Ross family in May 2011.<ref name=\"New Faces\" /> Before casting was finalized, there were numerous differences in the original concept for several of the characters.<ref name=\"New Faces\" /> The role of the mother to the Ross children was originally a photographer named \"Pandora\", the role of the oldest daughter, Emma, was originally named \"Anabel\", the role of Luke was originally a boy adopted from [[Korea]] named \"Hiro\", and the role of Ravi was originally a boy adopted from [[South America]] named \"Javier\" who had a pet [[capybara]] instead of a water monitor.<ref name=\"New Faces\" /><ref name=\"upfront\" /><ref name=\"PopCulturePassionistas.com 1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/PCPassionistas?feature=mhee#p/u/4/GovWKWXKV7E|title=An interview with Cameron Boyce from \"Jessie\"|date=September 28, 2011|work=PopCulturePassionistas.com}}</ref> Some have speculated that [[Brad Pitt]] and [[Angelina Jolie]], as a prominent celebrity couple with a multi-cultural adoptive family, may have been one possible inspiration for the series.<ref name=\"Boston Herald\" /> In an interview with the ''[[Boston Herald]]'', O'Connell described her inspiration, saying: \"I thought the celebrity parents and gorgeous penthouse would be glamorous, and a nice contrast to Jessie's more modest Texas roots. That fish out of water element makes for good stories, and I was inspired by many families who have adopted children of different ethnicities.\"<ref name=\"Boston Herald\" /> The Ross parents are only shown in a few episodes throughout the series.\n\n=== Filming ===\nAfter casting was finalized and changes were made to several of the characters to suit the actors chosen, the series skipped the pilot phase and was put directly into production.<ref name=\"PopCulturePassionistas.com 1\" /><ref name=\"Popstar Magazine\" /> Filming began in June 2011 on Stage 3/8 at [[Hollywood Center Studios]] which, prior to start of production, served as the sound stage where the Disney Channel series ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]'' was taped.<ref name=\"debby on Jessie\" /><ref name=\"production\" /> 13 episodes were originally ordered for the first season, but while the show's first season was in production, Disney Channel ordered an additional seven episodes, bringing the total number of episodes for the first season to 20.<ref name=\"Variety 1\" /> When asked about the atmosphere on set during an interview with ''[[MSN|MSN TV]]'', Ryan described her relationship with the young cast: \"I definitely feel like a nanny!  They are smart kids, but they're real kids. They like to have fun. My policy is: We can play hard, as long as we work hard, and because we work hard, we need to play hard.\"<ref name=\"MSN.com\" /> Filming on the series wrapped on February 22, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://instagram.com/p/zbczLZzXEK/?modal=true%7ctitle=Instagram%7cwork=Instagram|title=Instagram|accessdate=June 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn March 28, 2013, the series was renewed for a third season, with production resuming in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/03/28/jessie-renewed-by-disney-for-third-season/175468|title='Jessie' Renewed by Disney for Third Season|first=Amanda|last=Kondolojy|work=tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com|date=March 28, 2013|accessdate=March 28, 2013}}</ref> Season 3 premiered on October 5, 2013. On April 16, 2014, it was announced that Jessie would get engaged in a four-episode arc that would conclude the season in the fall, marking the first time a Disney Channel lead character has gotten engaged.<ref>{{cite news |first=Alyssa|last=Toomey |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/533225/disney-channel-s-jessie-to-feature-network-s-first-engagement |title=TV Scoop \u2013 Disney Channel's Jessie to Feature Network's First Engagement |work=E! Online |date=April 17, 2014 |accessdate=October 17, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe series was renewed for a fourth season on May 20, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/disney-channels-jessie-renewed-for-fourth-season-1201186573|title=Disney Channel's 'Jessie' Renewed for Fourth Season|first=Rick|last=Kissell|work=variety.com|date=May 20, 2014|accessdate=May 21, 2014}}</ref> Production began in August 2014 for a January 9, 2015 premiere. On October 1, 2014, Peyton List stated that the fourth season would be the last season of Jessie.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=090wTkKMGBc|title=Disney Star Peyton List Talks Last Season Of Jessie|publisher=fanlalatv|date=October 1, 2014|accessdate=November 6, 2014}}</ref> On January 9, 2015, Debby Ryan said that the fourth season will see the show go past its 100th episode and also see its fifth crossover with another Disney Channel show. She also stated that ''Jessie'' will end in early 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cp1OZdiuAx4|title= Jessie Cast Reveals Season 4 Details \u2013 INTERVIEW |publisher=Clevver News|date=January 9, 2015|accessdate=February 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn February 25, 2015, Disney Channel officially announced the series would end after its fourth season, bringing the series to a total of 101 episodes. On the same day, Disney ordered the first season of a spin-off titled ''[[Bunk'd|BUNK'd]]'', which stars Peyton List, Karan Brar, and Skai Jackson in their respective roles.<ref name=spinoff>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/02/jessie-cancelled-spinoff-peyton-list-karan-brar-skai-jackson-disney-channel-1201380940|title=Disney Channel's 'Jessie' Ending Run, But Spinoff Series Set With Stars Peyton List, Karan Brar & Skai Jackson|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|date=February 25, 2015|accessdate=February 25, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"tvline1\">{{cite web|last=Webb|first=Matt|url=http://tvline.com/2015/04/24/jessie-spinoff-bunkd-peyton-list-skai-jackson-karan-brar|title=Disney Channel's Jessie Spinoff Gets Title, Premise, Cast Additions|publisher=TVLine|date=April 24, 2015|accessdate=April 27, 2015}}</ref> 98 episodes were eventually aired in the series as 6 of the 101 produced episodes were combined into 3 extended length specials for broadcast and video sales.\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{main|List of Jessie episodes}}\n{{:List of Jessie episodes}}\n\n=== Crossovers ===\n\n==== Austin & Jessie & Ally All Star New Year ====\nIn November 2012, Disney Channel announced that the show would crossover with ''[[Austin & Ally]]'' as a one-hour special episode titled \"[[Austin & Jessie & Ally All Star New Year]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Disney Channel's Fa-la-la-lidays|url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/assets/pr%5Chtml/pr52566.html|work=Disney Channel MediaNet|publisher=disneychannelmedianet.com|accessdate=November 13, 2012}}</ref> The episode aired December 7, 2012.\n\n==== Good Luck Jessie: NYC Christmas ====\nIn October 2013, Disney Channel announced a crossover episode of ''Jessie'' and ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' called \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep59|Good Luck Jessie: NYC Christmas]]\". In the episode, [[Good Luck Charlie#PJ Duncan|PJ]] ([[Jason Dolley]]) and Teddy ([[Bridgit Mendler]]) go to New York for Christmas Eve and stay with Jessie for [[Christmas]] due to a snowstorm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Exclusive-Good-Luck-Charlie-Jessie-Crossover-1072603.aspx|title=Exclusive: Disney Channel Plots Good Luck Charlie and Jessie Holiday Crossover \u2013 Today's News: Our Take|publisher=TVGuide.com|date=October 28, 2013|accessdate=December 18, 2013}}</ref> The episode aired on November 29, 2013.\n\n==== Ultimate Spider-Man: Web-Warriors ====\nThe series crossed over with the [[Marvel Entertainment|Marvel]]/[[Disney XD]] series ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (TV series)|Ultimate Spider-Man: Web Warriors]]'' for a Halloween episode titled \"Halloween Night at the Museum\" on October 10, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jessie-Ultimate-Spider-Man-Web-Warriors-1087513.aspx|title=First Look: Disney Channel's ''Jessie'' Gets Animated on Marvel's ''Ultimate Spider Man: Web-Warriors''|first=Michael|last=Schneider|work=TV Guide|date=September 24, 2014|accessdate=September 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==== Jessie's Aloha-Holidays with Parker and Joey ====\nOn November 28, 2014, ''Jessie'' shared its fourth crossover with the series ''[[Liv and Maddie]]'' in a special episode titled \"Jessie's Aloha-Holidays with Parker and Joey\", featuring Joey Bragg as Joey Rooney and Tenzing Norgay Trainor as Parker Rooney.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9gdt7srN1N4|title=Disney Channel US \u2013 Jessie's Aloha-Holidays with Parker and Joey; Promo|work=[[YouTube]]|date=October 17, 2014|accessdate=October 25, 2014}}</ref> This crossover put ''Jessie'' into a tie with ''[[Hannah Montana]]'' and ''[[Lilo & Stitch: The Series]]'' as the Disney Channel shows to have had the most crossovers. This was counted as a single one-hour episode of ''Jessie'' with ''Liv and Maddie'' characters, and was not a ''Liv and Maddie'' episode.\n\n== Controversy ==\nDisney Channel did not broadcast \"Quitting Cold Koala\" on its originally scheduled date of May 17, 2013, and showed a rerun of \"Kids Don't Wanna Be Shunned\" instead. The episode did, however, appear on the Disney Channel website, \"WATCH Disney Channel\", and on \"Disney Channel on Demand\", the channel's [[video-on-demand]] service. On [[Facebook]], Disney Channel announced, \"We are removing this particular episode from our regular programming schedule and will re-evaluate its references to gluten restrictions in the character's diet\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-204_162-57585388/disney-pulls-jessie-episode-that-makes-fun-of-gluten-free-child |title=Disney pulls \"Jessie\" episode that makes fun of gluten-free child |date=May 20, 2013 |publisher=CBS news |first=Michelle |last=Castillo |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6GlcpaDAU?url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-204_162-57585388/disney-pulls-jessie-episode-that-makes-fun-of-gluten-free-child/ |url-status=live |archivedate=May 20, 2013 }}\n* See also: {{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/DisneyChannel/posts/632352486793221 |title=To our viewers |date=May 17, 2013 |accessdate=May 20, 2013 |publisher=Disney Channel official Facebook |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402211801/https://www.facebook.com/DisneyChannel/posts/632352486793221 |archivedate=April 2, 2015 }}</ref> The edited version of \"Quitting Cold Koala\" aired on July 5, 2013, as part of a two-episode spectacular, with all gluten jokes having been removed in the revised version.\n\n== Spin-off ==\nOn February 25, 2015, [[Disney Channel]] stated that a ''Jessie'' spin-off titled ''[[Bunk'd]]'' would begin production in the spring. The spin-off would star Peyton List, Karan Brar, and Skai Jackson.<ref name=spinoff/><ref name=\"tvline1\"/> The show premiered on July 31, 2015, right after the [[List of Disney Channel Original Movies|Disney Channel original movie]] ''[[Descendants (2015 film)|Descendants]]''.\n\n== Indian adaptation ==\nAn Indian adaptation of the show, titled ''[[Oye Jassie]]'', premiered on [[Disney Channel (India)|Disney Channel]] on October 13, 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/family-fun/article5226389.ece|title=Family fun|date=October 12, 2013|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref> Like most adaptations, the episodes and characters are similar to the original.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://data.disneyduniya.in/Harsh-Vashist-and-Simple-Kaul-to-feature-in-Disney-s-new-show-Oye-Jassi-tp4025207.html|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.is/20131001215130/http://data.disneyduniya.in/Harsh-Vashist-and-Simple-Kaul-to-feature-in-Disney-s-new-show-Oye-Jassi-tp4025207.html|archive-date=October 1, 2013|title=Jessie to premiere on October 11|work=Disneyduniya.in|accessdate=October 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nThe pilot episode of ''Jessie'' was released as a free download via the [[iTunes Store]] one week prior to its [[Disney Channel]] premiere. Making its official debut on the Disney Channel on September 30, 2011, the series became the network's most-watched premiere on a Friday since September 2008, when ''[[The Suite Life on Deck]]'' debuted.<ref name=\"Hollywood Reporter\" /><ref name=\"Variety 3\" />  The premiere of ''Jessie'' ranked as the number-one telecast at 9:00 PM with a total of 4.6 million total viewers in the target demographics, scoring 2.3 million viewers among kids 6\u201311, 1.8 million viewers among tweens and teens 9\u201314, and 887,000 viewers among adults 18\u201349.<ref name=\"Hollywood Reporter\" /><ref name=\"Variety 3\" /> The most watched episode of ''Jessie'' is \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep9|Star Wars]]\" with 7.32 million viewers total and the least watched episode is \"[[List of Jessie episodes#ep84|Basket Case]]\" with 1.38 million viewers total.\n\n== Broadcast ==\nThe series airs worldwide on [[Disney Channel]]. The series premiered on September 30, 2011, in [[Canada]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.family.ca/jessie|title=Jessie|work=family.ca|accessdate=May 21, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130518221403/http://www.family.ca/jessie/|archivedate=May 18, 2013}}</ref> on November 25, 2011, in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disney.com.au/DisneyChannel/jessie/?int_cmp=tv:jessie:May13:tvhome:charnav:6|title=Jessie \u2013 Disney Channel Australia|work=Disney.com.au|accessdate=May 21, 2013}}</ref> and on December 17, 2011, in [[Singapore]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneychannel-asia.com/DisneyChannel/supersites/jessie|title=Jessie Disney Channel Asia|work=Disneychannel-asia.com|access-date=May 12, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130406142919/http://www.disneychannel-asia.com/DisneyChannel/supersites/jessie/#|archive-date=April 6, 2013}}</ref> It later previewed on January 29, 2012, and premiered on February 17, 2012, in the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Ireland]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disney.co.uk/jessie|title=Jessie &#124; Disney Channel &#124; Disney UK|work=Disney.co.uk|accessdate=May 21, 2013}}</ref> and in [[South Africa]] on April 1, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disney.co.za/jessie/index.jsp|title=Jessie &#124; Disney Channel South Africa&#124; Home|work=Disney.co.za|accessdate=May 21, 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213923/http://www.disney.co.za/jessie/index.jsp#|archive-date=October 4, 2013}}</ref> In Canada, the series premiered on [[Disney Channel (Canada)|Disney Channel]] on September 1, 2015, and will be one of two series that Peyton List will introduce along with ''Bunk'd''.<ref name=DisneyCanadaStart>{{cite web |url=http://corusent.com/home/Corporate/PressReleases/tabid/1697/Default.aspx?Id=3055|title=Get Ready Canada! Disney Channel Arrives on September 1!|work=[[Corus Entertainment]]|date=August 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Ratings ==\n{{Television season ratings\n| hide_timeslot     = y\n| hide_tv_season    = y\n| hide_rank         = y\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n\n| link1             = List of Jessie episodes#Season 1 (2011\u201312)\n| episodes1         = 26<!-- should reflect the number of episodes that contribute to the average given in the last column -->\n| start1            = {{Start date|2011|9|30}}\n| end1              = {{End date|2012|9|7}}\n| startrating1      = 4.63<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2011/10/03/fridays-cable-ratings-alds-opens-on-top-for-tbs-567214/cable_20110930/|title=Friday's Cable Ratings|publisher=The Futon Critic|date=October 3, 2011|access-date=August 8, 2018}}</ref>\n| endrating1        = 3.59<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/09/10/fridays-cable-ratings-wwe-smackdown-disney-originals-lead-the-night-554414/cable_20120907/|title=Friday's Cable Ratings|publisher=The Futon Critic|date=September 10, 2012|access-date=August 8, 2018}}</ref>\n| viewers1          = {{decimals|{{#expr:((\n                      4.630 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 1 -->\n                      4.229 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 2 -->\n                      3.921 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 3 -->\n                      4.026 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 4 -->\n                      3.934 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 5 -->\n                      4.447 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 6 -->\n                      4.230 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 7 -->\n                      4.009 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 8 -->\n                      7.317 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 9 -->\n                      3.334 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 10 -->\n                      3.427 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 11 -->\n                      2.924 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 12 -->\n          